  "prompt": "My son has decided to discontinue 12std to pursue his internationally recognized and funded mobile innovation, should we support him?",
  "response": "This is a nuanced decision that requires careful consideration. Here are some points to weigh:\n\nPotential Positives:\n1. Direct entrepreneurial experience\n2. Active innovation in technology\n3. Potential early success\n4. Funding and recognition already in place\n5. Learning practical skills\n\nPotential Concerns:\n1. Importance of formal education\n2. Long-term career implications\n3. Backup plans if innovation doesn't succeed\n4. Competitive tech landscape\n\nRecommended Approach:\n1. Discuss detailed business plan\n2. Understand funding and mentorship\n3. Explore part-time educational options\n4. Set clear milestones and review progress\n5. Ensure he maintains educational pathway options\n6. Seek professional guidance\n\nKey Questions to Ask:\n- What specific innovation is he developing?\n- Who are his mentors/advisors?\n- What is the funding source?\n- What are the potential market opportunities?\n\nBalanced Support Strategy:\n- Encourage his entrepreneurial spirit\n- Ensure educational backup\n- Provide emotional and strategic support\n- Help him develop comprehensive skill set\n\nUltimately, supportive guidance with realistic expectations is crucial.\n\nWould you like to discuss this further?",
